00:56:47.000 --> 00:56:57.000
A lot of things were happening at the same time. So in the talk, I think I mostly focused on the implementation team and all the things that the implementation team was doing to get this

00:56:57.000 --> 00:57:02.000
from development to deployment. But there were different sub teams that were working on this.

00:57:02.000 --> 00:57:12.000
So there was the evaluation team, which is, you know, they were trying to address the question, like, how do we ensure that the ChartWatch deployment is successful?

00:57:12.000 --> 00:57:18.000
So they're the ones that are coming up with like, you know, we should measure vitals because you've got to measure clinical adherence in one way or another.

00:57:19.000 --> 00:57:27.000
And there was the modeling team, which is, you know, mostly the data science people and IT that are focused on actually building the model.

00:57:27.000 --> 00:57:44.000
So different teams working all at once. I see the way this all started is really from the general internal medicine doctor who came up with the idea first and came to the DSA team and said, like, hey, like, it would be cool if we had an early warning system.

00:57:44.000 --> 00:57:48.000
And then it's kind of like all snowballed into this.

00:57:50.000 --> 00:58:01.000
