00:58:24.000 --> 00:58:29.000
So we had all of the building blocks, we were assembling it together, that kind of happened a bit later.

00:58:31.000 --> 00:58:39.000
So on the topic of the team building, then, can you speak to any lessons learned from building four teams within DSA?

00:58:39.000 --> 00:58:44.000
What did it take for leadership or management to take on a big scale project like ChartWatch?

00:58:46.000 --> 00:58:51.000
Yeah, that's a great question. So when we first started off, we did not have the four team structure.

00:58:51.000 --> 00:58:55.000
It was, we just had data scientists to do a bit of everything.

00:58:57.000 --> 00:59:02.000
We found that, you know, there were certain people who were a lot more knowledgeable in one aspect.

00:59:03.000 --> 00:59:07.000
So I think it just made sense to split it up into this four different teams.

00:59:09.000 --> 00:59:13.000
And then within each of the teams, there is a director for each of these teams.

00:59:13.000 --> 00:59:20.000
I think it makes the management and coordination a lot more streamlined.

00:59:21.000 --> 00:59:24.000
So as a data scientist, I can focus on doing data science work.

00:59:24.000 --> 00:59:28.000
I don't need to think about all the other unrelated things.

00:59:30.000 --> 00:59:34.000
Absolutely. And I see Rebecca asked a question over on YouTube.

00:59:34.000 --> 00:59:38.000
